summary: In this context, 2-ethylhexan-1-ol and n-dodecane are both mentioned as standard compounds used in the analysis of volatile organic metabolites (VOMs) in malignant and benign effusions. However, there is no direct discussion of their relationship or interaction within the study. They are part of a broader analysis aimed at differentiating lung cancer patients from those with inflammatory conditions, but their specific roles or connections are not elaborated upon.
